title: Temple wallops Tulane 49-10
text:
Temple raised its record to 5-0 after rolling the Wave. The Owls defeated the Green Wave 49-10. (Photo by Mitchell Leff/Getty Images) *** Local Caption *** Sean Chandler;Sherman Badie (Photo: Mitchell Leff) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
PHILADELPHIA (AP) - Jahad Thomas and Ryquell Armstead scored two touchdowns apiece and Temple remained unbeaten with a 49-10 victory over Tulane on Saturday. 
The Owls (5-0, 2-0 American) are off to their first 5-0 start since 1974 after ending a two-game win streak for the Green Wave (2-3, 1-1). 
Thomas ran 10 yards to give Temple a 14-10 lead in the second quarter and added 16-yard scoring catch from P.J. Walker for a 21-10 halftime lead. 
The Owls held Tulane to just 8 yards rushing and eight first downs. Tyler Matakevich, playing just into the third quarter, made seven tackles, giving him 399 for his career, tops in the nation among active NCAA players. 
Tanner Lee was 16-of-29 passing for only 95 yards, one TD and two interceptions. Read or Share this story: http://on.wwltv.com/1LolrDm TOP VIDEOS
